headlines.description: — Khris Middleton and Bilal Coulibaly each scored 17 points and the Washington Wizards defeated the Charlotte Hornets 113-100 on Saturday night in a matchup of the NBA’s two worst teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton and Coulibaly each score 17 points as Wizards hand Hornets 6th straight defeat, 113-110

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham broke out of a slump by scoring nine of his 15 points in the fourth quarter and the Detroit Pistons pulled away to beat the Brooklyn Nets 115-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham breaks out of slump to lead Pistons past Nets 115-94

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 21 points and the Sacramento Kings overcome an early injury to Domantas Sabonis for their third straight victory, 113-103 over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings overcome the loss of Sabonis to beat the Rockets 113-103 for their 3rd straight victory

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox broke a tie with a 20-footer with 2.6 seconds left for the last of his 20 points and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Memphis Grizzlies 130-128 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De'Aaron Fox hits 20-footer with 2.6 seconds left in the Spurs' 130-128 victory over the Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Quentin Grimes scored a career-high 44 points and the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a nine-game losing streak, beating the Golden State Warriors 126-119 on Saturday night in a game where <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Grimes scores career-high 44 points and the 76ers beat the Warriors to end a 9-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 29 points, nine rebounds and nine assists, Damian Lillard scored 28 and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Dallas Mavericks 132-117 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo and Lillard lead Bucks to 132-117 victory over short-handed Mavericks
